snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService getAccount Sample
snippets.description: Lookup for a single Account.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService listAccounts Sample
snippets.description: Returns all accounts accessible by the caller. Note that these accounts might not currently have GA4 properties. Soft-deleted (ie: "trashed") accounts are excluded by default. Returns an empty list if no relevant accounts are found.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService deleteAccount Sample
snippets.description: Marks target Account as soft-deleted (ie: "trashed") and returns it. This API does not have a method to restore soft-deleted accounts. However, they can be restored using the Trash Can UI. If the accounts are not restored before the expiration time, the account and all child resources (eg: Properties, GoogleAdsLinks, Streams, UserLinks) will be permanently purged. https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6154772 Returns an error if the target is not found.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService updateAccount Sample
snippets.description: Updates an account.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService provisionAccountTicket Sample
snippets.description: Requests a ticket for creating an account.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService listAccountSummaries Sample
snippets.description: Returns summaries of all accounts accessible by the caller.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService getProperty Sample
snippets.description: Lookup for a single "GA4" Property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService listProperties Sample
snippets.description: Returns child Properties under the specified parent Account. Only "GA4" properties will be returned. Properties will be excluded if the caller does not have access. Soft-deleted (ie: "trashed") properties are excluded by default. Returns an empty list if no relevant properties are found.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService createProperty Sample
snippets.description: Creates an "GA4" property with the specified location and attributes.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService deleteProperty Sample
snippets.description: Marks target Property as soft-deleted (ie: "trashed") and returns it. This API does not have a method to restore soft-deleted properties. However, they can be restored using the Trash Can UI. If the properties are not restored before the expiration time, the Property and all child resources (eg: GoogleAdsLinks, Streams, UserLinks) will be permanently purged. https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6154772 Returns an error if the target is not found, or is not an GA4 Property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService updateProperty Sample
snippets.description: Updates a property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService getUserLink Sample
snippets.description: Gets information about a user's link to an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService batchGetUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Gets information about multiple users' links to an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService listUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Lists all user links on an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService auditUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Lists all user links on an account or property, including implicit ones that come from effective permissions granted by groups or organization admin roles. If a returned user link does not have direct permissions, they cannot be removed from the account or property directly with the DeleteUserLink command. They have to be removed from the group/etc that gives them permissions, which is currently only usable/discoverable in the GA or GMP UIs.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService createUserLink Sample
snippets.description: Creates a user link on an account or property. If the user with the specified email already has permissions on the account or property, then the user's existing permissions will be unioned with the permissions specified in the new UserLink.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService batchCreateUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Creates information about multiple users' links to an account or property. This method is transactional. If any UserLink cannot be created, none of the UserLinks will be created.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService updateUserLink Sample
snippets.description: Updates a user link on an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService batchUpdateUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Updates information about multiple users' links to an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService deleteUserLink Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a user link on an account or property.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService batchDeleteUserLinks Sample
snippets.description: Deletes information about multiple users' links to an account or property.

snippets.description: Creates a DisplayVideo360AdvertiserLink. Users who do not have access to the Display & Video 360 advertiser should instead seek to create a DisplayVideo360LinkProposal.

snippets.title: AnalyticsAdminService runAccessReport Sample
snippets.description: Returns a customized report of data access records. The report provides records of each time a user reads Google Analytics reporting data. Access records are retained for up to 2 years. Data Access Reports can be requested for a property. The property must be in Google Analytics 360. This method is only available to Administrators. These data access records include GA4 UI Reporting, GA4 UI Explorations, GA4 Data API, and other products like Firebase & Admob that can retrieve data from Google Analytics through a linkage. These records don't include property configuration changes like adding a stream or changing a property's time zone. For configuration change history, see [searchChangeHistoryEvents](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/config/admin/v1/rest/v1alpha/accounts/searchChangeHistoryEvents).
